name: I'm Not A Big Fan of the Heat
description: There are fires for burning and fires for flaying, fire for flashing and for lying. There are lips vying for your attention. Pay attention. You lay in the field of breezes and wait for the trees to caress your carcass, your bones longing to melt into the soft bush, you wait to be coddled and moistened by their sweet flesh and melt away. But instead you are in a building, burning in the city center, your back full of nails, and you are melting into the flame, waiting again, waiting to be worn into the weave of smoke. Or.
